dcterms:description: The classical Private Information Retrieval (PIR) problem where a user wants to retrieve one message from a set of K messages stored on one or more servers without revealing which message is being retrieved.

dcterms:title: PIR with Private Side Information (PIR-PSI)

dcterms:creator: S. Kadhe
B. Garcia
A. Heidarzadeh
S. El Rouayheb
A. Sprintson
dcterms:description: Private Information Retrieval with Side Information (PIR-SI) where the identity of none of the side information messages needs to be kept private.
dcterms:title: PIR with Side Information (PIR-SI)

dcterms:creator: K. Banawan
S. Ulukus
dcterms:description: Multi-message private information retrieval where a user retrieves multiple messages from a set of K messages stored on one or more servers.
dcterms:title: Multi-message private information retrieval

dcterms:creator: S. P. Shariatpanahi
M. J. Siavoshani
M. A. Maddah-Ali
dcterms:description: Multi-message private information retrieval with private side information where the identities of all side information messages must be kept private.

dcterms:creator: S. Li
M. Gastpar
dcterms:description: Single-server multi-message private information retrieval with side information where the identity of none of the side information messages needs to be kept private.
dcterms:title: Single-server multi-message private information retrieval with side information

S. Kadhe

dcterms:creator: R. Tandon
dcterms:description: Cache-aided private information retrieval where a user retrieves messages from a server with the help of a cache.

K. Banawan

dcterms:description: Cache-aided private information retrieval with partially known uncoded prefetching where some information is pre-fetched to help in retrieval.
